On 2/19/2011 3:14 PM, Max Bronsema wrote:
> Swapped the ignition switch red wire for the red one on the supply side.
> Bus still starts and all functions work. I found the red wire from the

If you just swapped the wires that connect to the supply side of fuses 8 
and 9, you did nothing because the supply side of those fuses are bused 
(connected) with a copper bar.  Remove fuses 7, 8, and 9 and if the bus 
won't start, you've got a problem.
